The Houston office is located in Greenspoint.[9]
In March 2015, Nabors said it plans to cut 3,500 jobs in response to falling upstream activity amid slumping oil prices. The company will cut 10 percent of its sales staff and 20 percent of its U.S. drilling workforce.[10]
